/*
Problem- 424.Longest Repeating character Replacement
Frequency-11ms
Platform-Leetcode
Difficulty- Medium

Approach- Sliding window

Maintain a frequency array (arr[26]) to count occurrences of characters in the current window.
Use two pointers:
left → start of window
right → end of window
Track maxfrequency:
the highest frequency of a single character inside the window.
Check if the window is valid:
window size - maxfrequency <= k
Meaning:
characters that need replacement ≤ k.
If replacements needed become greater than k, shrink the window:
decrease frequency of s[left]
move left++.
Update the maximum window length as the result.

Solution-*/
class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {
       int arr[]=new int[26];
       int left=0,result=0,maxfrequency=0;

       for(int right=0;s.length()>right;right++){
        arr[s.charAt(right)-'A']++;
        maxfrequency=Math.max(maxfrequency, arr[s.charAt(right)-'A']);
        if(right-left+1-maxfrequency>k){
             arr[s.charAt(left)-'A']--;
             left++;
        }
        result=Math.max(result,right-left+1);
       }
       return result;
    }
}
